This is a great collection for fans of the show. I personally binge-watched all ten hours without once getting off the couch.  I don't know if it was the lack of food, or bathroom breaks, but afterward I fell into a deep sleep where I dreamt that I was a sleazy lounge singer and my band was all four Golden Girls. Estelle Getty was beating the skins on a kit that would rival Neil Peart's. Betty White was on upright bass, Rue McClanahan was blowin' smoky jazz on a sax, and Bea Arthur was playing keys with her right foot like only Jerry Lee Lewis or a really tall feminist could do! I can't promise that you will have the same awesome dreams and hallucinations that I had after buying this set, but I'm guessing you will. Enjoy!

I ordered Season 6 and 7...twice. The first time they arrived I could hear something shaking inside, assumed broken DVD...no, the plastic parts that hold the CD in place were smashed into pieces which in turn had scratched the DVDs. The other one was broken also but just the plastic hinge in the middle, but too much to fix do I returned them both. Assuming it was just my package that was unlucky, I reordered and returned. Here's the thing, Im not
going to send them back again and expect different results. These DVD sets are BROKEN. ....I settled on good enough after inspection, lucked out no scratches.

Golden Girls is my FAVORITE show, so I was very excited when my package arrived. It came in pristine condition. The first DVD played beautifully.. the second DVD played beautifully. And today I began to start on the third DVD and it won't play. My DVD player won't recognize it. My mothers DVD player won't recognize it. I've tried 4 DVD plays so far (all different brands) and nothing. This is such a bummer. I had planned on purchasing the entire series over the course of a few months (one season a month), however I will NOT be purchasing them from this seller again. Why buy something that is defective?
